<!-- only part below is in the sourceforge site docs ->

You will only need the sword libraries when you compile BibleTime yourself using the source package. Sword is statically linked into the BibleTime rpms and therefore you do not need to install the sword libraries when you use the BibleTime rpms.

<h3>BibleTime 1.0.x</h3>

<LI><a href="http://www.trolltech.com/">Qt 2.2x or later </A></LI>
<LI><a href="http://www.kde.org/">KDE 2.x</A></LI>
<LI><a href="http://www.crosswire.org/sword/download/ftpmirror/pub/sword/source/v1.5/sword-1.5.2.tar.gz">Sword 1.5.2</A></LI>

<h3>BibleTime 0.3x</h3>

<LI><a href="http://www.trolltech.com/">Qt 2.22 or later</A></LI>
<LI><a href="http://www.kde.org/">KDE 2.x</A></LI>
<LI><a href="http://www.crosswire.org/">Sword 1.51a</A></LI>

<h3>BibleTime 0.2x</h3>

<LI><a href="http://www.trolltech.com/">Qt 2.22 or later</A></LI>
<LI><a href="http://www.kde.org/">KDE 1.x</A></LI>
<LI><a href="http://www.crosswire.org/">Sword 1.50</A></LI>

<!-- only part above is in the sourceforge site docs ->
